**Refining App Name**

I'm currently focused on the application's branding, specifically the title. I'm updating the `metadata` to reflect the change from "Disaster AI" to "Crisis AI." I've updated the source code, but I am now re-reviewing the code for any instances that use the existing title.


**Implementing Map Integration**

I've shifted focus to integrating the map feature. I've decided to use Leaflet, which is simpler and already available, instead of diving into the Google Maps React SDK. I'm working on a new `LiveMap.tsx` component that will handle displaying alerts on the map. I'll need to update the `Alert` type definition in `types.ts` to include latitude and longitude, and then update the mock data in `constants.ts` with some placeholder coordinates.


**Updating Application Title**

I've completed the title change. I updated `metadata.json`, `index.html`, and `Header.tsx` to reflect "Crisis AI." Now, I'm verifying all instances for any potential lingering references to the old title within the code. Then I will start working on the Google Maps integration.



**Implementing Map Integration**

